Okechukwu Nnodim, Abuja The Federal Government on Wednesday inaugurated the board of the Nigerian Electricity Management Services Agency. Minister of State for Power, Goddy Jeddy-Agba, inaugurated the new board in Abuja. A newly constituted management team for the agency was also inaugurated. Jedy-Agba said the board and the management team of the NEMSA must work in tandem with stipulated laws to achieve the goal of the agency. He charged the board to avoid conflicting with the management of the power services agency. Copyright PUNCH.
